            <title>[THRIFT-1208] python TCompactProtocol.py writeBool and readBool not follow the compact-proto-spec-2.txt spec for CONTAINER_WRITE, CONTAINER_READ </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1208</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12399869/compact-proto-spec-2.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12399869/compact-proto-spec-2.txt&lt;/a&gt;, define the boolean value as follow:&lt;br/&gt;
boolean-true          =&amp;gt; 0x1&lt;br/&gt;
boolean-false         =&amp;gt; 0x2&lt;br/&gt;
But in TCompactProtocol.py writeBool, readBool for CONTAINER_WRITE, CONTAINER_READ just bool(0x2) will always get true.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
